Office of Admissions Address: Florida State University Office of Admissions A2500 University Center 282 Champions Way Tallahassee FL 32306-2400 Phone: 850-644-6200 Fax: 850-644-0197 Email: admissions@fsu.edu
Seminole Dining Address: Seminole Dining Membership Office 104 N Woodward Ave Tallahassee, Florida 32306 Phone: 850-644-3663 Fax: 850-644-4999 Email: seminoledining@fsu.edu
University Registrar Address: Office of the University Registrar Florida State University Room A3900 UCA 282 Champions Way PO Box 3062400 Tallahassee, FL 32306-2400 Phone: 850-644-1050

The FSU bookstore carries all the text books and class resources you'll need for your classes here at FSU. They have a wide range of official FSU merchandise and everything you need for a garnet & gold tailgate. The bookstore also contains an on-site apple store as well as a repair center for your personal tech support needs.
http://www.bkstr.com/floridastatestore/home

If you're looking to set up a meal plan for easy, no hassle food on campus Seminole Dining is your one stop shop. http://seminoledining.campusdish.com/
Looking for the best food on a budget? Look no further. https://www.tripadvisor.com/Restaurants-g34675-Tallahassee_Florida.html#MAINWRAP
If it's late night and your on a budget Guthries is a Tallahassee classic. http://www.guthrieschicken.com/

More than just football the Seminoles excel in many sports. Show your support by attending events and wearing your colors. With a schedule for all the events and ticket sales the FSU Athletics website has everything you need to bleed garnet and gold!
Check it out: http://www.seminoles.com/

Start planning your vacations ahead of time. Check the academic calendar for holidays and school wide deadlines. If you want to you can even syncronize the academic calendar with your own through Microsoft Outlook.
http://calendar.fsu.edu/Lists/Academics/calendar.aspx

Lost? Use the interactive campus map to find where you're headed. It includes all the important stops around campus and the 3 letter building codes for any you don't recognize on your schedule. A must visit site for any new freshman.
http://campus.map.fsu.edu/index.aspx

Get from point A to point B with FSU Transportation & Parking services. Find student parking lots and the closest bus route with their interactive maps. It's also the place to go to keep your parking permit up to date (or pay a citation in case you forgot).
https://transportation.fsu.edu/
